                            <comment id="15007950" author="smilegator" created="Tue, 17 Nov 2015 03:36:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I can try it if this is not an urgent issue. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15007953" author="zeocio" created="Tue, 17 Nov 2015 03:37:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Took a quick look with jackson-core 2.4.4, the following work for both the off and on tests: NaN, Infinity, +Infinity, -Infinity.  However +INF and -INF don&apos;t work for me for some reason.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15007958" author="rxin" created="Tue, 17 Nov 2015 03:42:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t think this is urgent, so take your time. Note that we also have some custom code to handle NaN in the json parser ourselves. Ideally we should remove those code and just let Jackson handle them.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/540bf58f18328c68107d6c616ffd70f3a4640054/sql/core/src/main/scala/org/apache/spark/sql/execution/datasources/json/JacksonParser.scala#L102&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/540bf58f18328c68107d6c616ffd70f3a4640054/sql/core/src/main/scala/org/apache/spark/sql/execution/datasources/json/JacksonParser.scala#L102&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
